		</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="2">Part 2</a>,									Keius' adversaries inside the prototype time dilation field destroy the civilization inside the field, and in their wake a more hostile alien life form evolves.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="2/1">Episode 1</a>,											the prototype time dilation field is activated, and within it Goran and his conspirators begin their plan, but it quickly goes completely awry.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/2">Episode 2</a>,											after the Ehrban inside the time bubble kill each other off in a vicious civil war, their half-dragon mutant creations evolve over geological time into a hostile alien species, the Berol.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/3">Episode 3</a>,											the Berol discover and deactivate the time dilation field they evolved within, and discovering the rest of the universe for the first time, promptly declare war on it.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="3">Part 3</a>,									the hostile new aliens escape from inside the time dilation field and lay seige to an unsuspecting galaxy, destroying all of Ehrban civilization.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="3/1">Episode 1</a>,											a mere instant after activating the time dilation field, the hostile Berol fleet suddenly appear and begin to pour out to attack the Ehrban.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/2">Episode 2</a>,											as the innumerable Berol quickly overwhelm the unsuspecting Ehrban, Keius orders the wormhole network deactivated, and the Asiron to exterminate the new threat.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/3">Episode 3</a>,											Ehrba is destroyed by the attacking Berol, save Tatia and a handful of mages, and Keius abandons his humans at Earth to return to Ehrba at subluminal speeds.										</li>									</ol>								</li>							</ol>						</li>					</ol>				</section><? require $_SERVER['DOCUMENT_ROOT'] . "/includes/footer-global.php" ?>